  "name": "Effect: Dragonflight Meditation",
  "type": "effect",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\">You internalize the parables of the dragon’s greed, and enter a trance. You connect with the magic that flows through dragons and their curse. In your trance, you contend with and face that inner-turmoil, and bask in the draconic presence that grows with your contemplations.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:initial;scrollbar-color:initial;margin:0.5em 0px;color:rgb(25, 24, 19);font-family:Roboto, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;white-space:normal;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\">When you cast this spell, you gain 2 Zeal. Select one of the following curses of the drachiri: wealth, fame, power, pleasure, vengeance, or knowledge. This represents the curse and type of drachiri you are internalizing throughout the spell’s duration. Once per round when you cast this spell or when you sustain this spell, you can evoke one of the following recitations, and channel a representation of the dragon’s struggle. You can only choose Soar and one other recitation, depending on your chosen curse.</span></p>"
